# Project Integrity

## Directory Structure — Never Break

```
src/
  mlmodel.py          # inference entrypoint only
  models/             # one file per model class
params/
  ml_params.yaml      # params placeholder, keep minimal
dataset/              # read-only, never modify
notebooks/            # one per author/experiment
res_perf/             # performance outputs only
outputs/submissions/  # submission CSVs only
ai/
  rules/
  skills/
```

## Rules

- `dataset/` is **read-only** — never write, move, or delete files there
- `src/mlmodel.py` dispatches only — no model logic inside it
- New models go in `src/models/` following `BaseFraudModel` interface
- `params/ml_params.yaml` stays minimal — no hardcoded paths elsewhere
- Submissions always go to `outputs/submissions/submission.csv`
- Performance artifacts (metrics, plots, feature importances) go to `res_perf/`
- Never commit trained model artifacts (`.joblib`) — already in `.gitignore`
